{"cursor":"9983","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Millenarianism' (also 'millenarism'), from Latin \"containing a thousand\", is\nthe belief by a religious, social, or political group or movement in a coming\nmajor transformation of society, after which all things will be changed, based\non a one-thousand-year cycle. The term is more generically used to refer to any\nbelief centered around 1000-year intervals. Millenarianism is a concept or theme\nthat exists in many cultures and religions. '[[Millennialism]]' is a specific\ntype of Christian millenarianism, and is sometimes referred to as 'Chiliasm'\nfrom the New Testament use of the Greek \"chilia\"\n(thousand). [http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/10307a.htm]\n","linknr":233,"url":"Millenarianism","recorded":1374780631,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Millenarianism&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Millenarianism&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Millerism","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Millenarianism&action=edit","/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1","/wiki/Template:Citation_needed","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiab